posts.name: John Bottenberg
posts.cooked:
It seems like you would be able to get the most accurate angle by using trigonometry.

I doubt even this would be perfect, though. Unless you’re launching notes at infinite speed, the notes will follow rough parabolas (ballistic trajectories) in flight instead of straight lines. I’m not sure what the effect of air resistance is, but that might matter as well.

This is why people are saying to use empirically derived angles based on actually shooting the notes from various positions, trying different angles until they consistently go in.
yeah, the solution i was considering was PIDing the arm to a certain angle, and then seeing what was the most consistent, so i could use that
